acob sod pottage: and Esau came from the field, and he was faint:","year":-1805},{"id":"recCGvTcvTTYifiSm","ref":"Gen.25.30","text":"And Esau said to Jacob, Feed me, I pray thee, with that same red pottage; for I am faint: therefore was his name called Edom.","year":-1805},{"id":"recKGLoZNwgNdY10B","ref":"Gen.25.31","text":"And Jacob said, Sell me this day thy birthright.","year":-1805},{"id":"recKN0KeTi11uxzud","ref":"Gen.25.33","text":"And Jacob said, Swear to me this day; and he sware unto him: and he sold his birthright unto Jacob.","year":-1805},{"id":"recmY4BRLoklAYX3N","ref":"Gen.25.34","text":"Then Jacob gave Esau bread and pottage of lentiles; and he did eat and drink, and rose up, and went his way: thus Esau despised his birthright.","year":-1805}]}
